3. Monitoring Scope Breakdown
Databases & Storage
* PostgreSQL (keystone, airflow, superset): Connection health, replication lag, WAL growth
* ClickHouse: Query load, memory usage, migration issues
* RabbitMQ: Queue depth, memory usage
* PVCs: Usage %, bound capacity
Services & Applications
* Airflow: DAG failures, scheduler downtime, worker restarts
* Internal APIs: Auth failures, request errors
* UI Apps: Page load times, service errors
* Logging Pipelines: Fluent Bit & Loki ingestion delays, dropped logs
Nodes
* CPU usage trends
* Memory saturation
* Network pressure
* Disk I/O errors
Alerting
* PagerDuty escalation triggers
* Error types
* Alert grouping and routing by severity

4. When to Worry – Alert Thresholds
Alert Level

	Condition

	Example Actions

🔴 Red (Critical)
	Metric exceeds 80% of capacity
	Immediate action. PagerDuty alert triggered. Investigate CPU, memory, disk issues.

🟠 Orange (Warning)
	Metric between 60%–80%
	Investigate soon. No PagerDuty unless sustained. Review logs and trends.

🟢 Green (Normal)
	Metric below 60%
	No action needed. Continue monitoring.

Threshold Examples
Metric

	🟢 Green (<60%)

	🟠 Orange (60–80%)

	🔴 Red (>80%)

CPU Usage
	Stable
	Monitor
