	Free up/expand

Replication Lag
	Normal
	Monitor
	Fix immediately

5. Commands for Manual Monitoring
Pod & Node Health
kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
 kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>
 kubectl get nodes
 kubectl top pods -n <namespace>
 kubectl top nodes

Logging Verification

 kubectl logs <pod-name> -n <namespace>
 kubectl logs -f <pod-name> -n <namespace>

Storage Checks

 kubectl get pvc -n <namespace>
 df -h

6. PagerDuty Alerts, Escalations & Policies
* Alerts grouped by severity
* Primary on-call escalation within 15 minutes
* Emergency escalation after 1 hour
* Dummy pods simulate failures to test routing

7. Communication Process
* Acknowledge PagerDuty alerts immediately
* Share updates via JIRA
* Post-incident summary and corrective actions

8. Continuous Improvement
* Quarterly review of metrics and thresholds
* Document lessons learned
* Keep Confluence updated with rule/responsibility changes

📌 Note:
This guide applies to Dev, QA, Staging, and Production environments
